After carrying out the experiments suggested by Design Expert software, the observed responses were recorded (Table 2). From these responses, the software automatically suggests a model which is a good-fitting mathematical function relating the response with the input factors tested. Predicted responses are then calculated from this fitted equation (Table 2) and used to estimate residuals and construct statistical and graphical summaries by the Design Expert software. The coefficients in this equation compensate for the differences in the ranges of the factors as well as the differences in the effects. These coefficients cannot be intuitively interpreted due to their dependence on the scaling of the factor levels (https://www.statease.com/pubs/handbk_for_exp_sv.pdf). This fitted equation is given by Eq 1:1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
